8. A method of determining a gate capacitance of a MOS transistor, comprising:
(a) measuring a measured capacitance and a measured dissipation factor of the MOS transistor;
(b) setting an initial capacitance;
(c) calculating a calculated capacitance and a calculated dissipation factor based on the initial capacitance;
(d) repeating steps (b) and (c) until both the calculated capacitance is equal to the measured capacitance and the calculated dissipation factor is equal to the measured dissipation factor; and
(e) detecting the initial capacitance as an accurate gate capacitance of the MOS transistor when it is determined that both the calculated capacitance is equal to the measured capacitance and the calculated dissipation factor is equal to the measured dissipation factor.
